This article is a presidential proclamation issued by President Barack Obama in response to the terrorist attack in Brussels, Belgium on March 22, 2016. The proclamation expresses solidarity with the people of Brussels and a commitment to bringing the perpetrators of the attack to justice. As a mark of respect for the victims, the proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at various locations, including the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts and naval stations, and naval vessels. The flag will remain at half-staff until sunset on March 26, 2016. The proclamation also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad for the same length of time.